In [[Reformed]] [[Christian ethics]], the '''creation mandates''' or '''creation ordinances''' are the commandments given to [[Adam and Eve]] in [[Genesis creation narrative|Genesis 1 and 2]]. These predate the [[Mosaic Law]] and are often thought to apply to all people rather than just Christians. They include the [[cultural mandate]], including [[Christian views on marriage|marriage]] and procreation (Gen 1:28), the [[Vocation#Christian views on work|labour mandate]] (Gen 2:15), and the [[Sabbath in Christianity|Sabbath]] (Gen 2:3).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Murray |first1=John |authorlink1=John Murray (theologian) |title=Principles of Conduct: Aspects of Biblical Ethics |date=1957 |pages=27-44}}</ref>
